<node id="Cutting-Edge Technology">
  <data key="d0">Cutting-Edge Technology</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cutting-edge technology refers to advanced innovations and developments utilized by athletes to enhance their performance. This encompasses a range of technological advancements designed specifically to help athletes achieve peak performance levels, including tools and equipment such as carbon-fiber spikes. These innovative solutions are particularly noted for improving athletic performance in events like the 100-meter sprint. Athletes such as Noah Carter have employed cutting-edge technology, including his carbon-fiber spikes, to break records and achieve superior results. The term encapsulates various advanced technological advancements that provide significant performance advantages in athletics.&lt;SEP&gt;Cutting-edge technology refers to the advanced innovations such as carbon-fiber spikes used by Noah Carter.&lt;SEP&gt;The use of cutting-edge technology like carbon-fiber spikes represents advancements in athletic equipment designed to enhance performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Cutting-edge technology refers to the advanced innovations used by athletes to enhance performance, such as carbon-fiber spikes.</data>
