  <data key="d0">A部門</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-daa296a353c26f41dfc613743d24e936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d96ca3133c54d9d76add7de434ee05b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-333af5cc1ff286e512f36be66d1aa78b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7504d68fad10caa1cd0ea41314ed2ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2940790b50eb2cba2a5e944b95a94dd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72f381579d364fa91cc3e73153e0af97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f62a98ad02d11a4c9618cbda43281859&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf168eec40aae386455af5027929f6fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ebe784b7ece61edcdd2e054763c0ce3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95280ea367581dac710f0dc56c7a72f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942b136689124792272bc32a2898842c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3781d1671ca7126e99e7656264965fb6</data>
  <data key="d2">A部門 is an organizational unit within B客户的 organization responsible for performing various maintenance tasks and activities to ensure system functionality, reliability, and overall architecture. The department conducts regular maintenance checks such as联动主机检查to maintain system health and performs Splunk-related tasks including the adjustment and upgrade of IP configurations. A部門 involves personnel such as A人员and C人员in carrying out these responsibilities and is also accountable for certain reports related to B客户的 systems. Additionally, during onsite visits, specific maintenance services are provided by or within A部門.&lt;SEP&gt;A部門is a department mentioned in the maintenance record, where specific tasks related to Splunk and user permissions are being conducted.&lt;SEP&gt;A部門is a department where one of the tasks involved confirming and sending account inventory reports.&lt;SEP&gt;A部門is a department that deals with certain maintenance actions for B客戶.</data>
