<node id="Carbon-Fiber Spikes">
  <data key="d0">Carbon-Fiber Spikes</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Carbon-Fiber Spikes are advanced sprinting shoes designed to enhance the speed and performance of athletes, particularly in sprint events. Made from carbon fiber, these shoes offer significant improvements in both traction and speed due to their high-performance materials and design. Carbon-Fiber Spikes are widely used by competitive athletes aiming to gain a competitive edge, as they provide unparalleled support for quick acceleration and rapid movement. Notably, Noah Carter utilized Carbon-Fiber Spikes to break the 100m sprint record, further highlighting their effectiveness in achieving exceptional athletic performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Advanced sprinting shoes made from carbon fiber that provide enhanced speed and traction.&lt;SEP&gt;Advanced sprinting shoes made from carbon fiber that provide enhanced speed and traction.&lt;SEP&gt;Carbon-fiber spikes are advanced sprinting shoes used by Noah Carter to break the 100m sprint record.&lt;SEP&gt;Advanced sprinting shoes made of carbon fiber that enhance speed and traction.&lt;SEP&gt;Advanced sprinting shoes that provide enhanced speed and traction for athletes.</data>
